# Privacy Policy

Last updated: March 27, 2026

Sno Development ("we," "our," or "us") values your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, share, and protect information when you use our mobile applications, websites, and related services (collectively, the "Services").

This policy is written to be reused across multiple apps. Where needed, app-specific details are listed in the "App-Specific Addendum" section.

## 1. Scope

This Privacy Policy applies to all Services published, operated, or managed by Sno Development, unless a different privacy policy is shown in a specific app or service.

## 2. Information We Collect

Depending on the app and your settings, we may collect:

### A. Information You Provide
- Account details (such as email address, display name, login credentials)
- Content you create, upload, or manage in the app
- Support requests and messages you send us
- Purchase or subscription details (processed by app stores/payment providers)

### B. Automatically Collected Information
- Device information (device model, OS version, language, app version)
- App usage data (features used, session length, screens viewed, interactions)
- Technical and diagnostic data (crash logs, performance metrics, error reports)
- Approximate location inferred from IP address

### C. Data from Third Parties
- App store information (purchase status, subscription status)
- Authentication providers (if social or third-party sign-in is used)
- Advertising/analytics partners (as permitted by your consent and settings)

## 3. How We Use Information

We use information to:
- Provide, maintain, and improve the Services
- Enable core app functionality and user support
- Process transactions, subscriptions, and restore purchases
- Personalize app experience and content
- Measure usage and performance
- Detect, prevent, and address fraud, abuse, and security incidents
- Comply with legal obligations and enforce our terms

## 4. Legal Bases (Where Required)

Where laws like the GDPR apply, we process personal data based on one or more of:
- Your consent
- Performance of a contract (providing requested Services)
- Legitimate interests (service improvement, security, fraud prevention)
- Compliance with legal obligations

## 5. Sharing of Information

We do not sell personal data in exchange for money. We may share data with:
- Service providers (hosting, analytics, crash reporting, customer support)
- Payment processors and app store platforms (Google Play, Apple App Store)
- Advertising partners (for ad delivery/measurement, where applicable)
- Legal authorities, if required by law or to protect rights/safety
- Successors in case of merger, acquisition, or asset transfer

## 6. Third-Party SDKs and Services

Our apps may use third-party SDKs/services such as analytics, crash reporting, advertising, cloud storage, authentication, and billing tools.

Examples may include (depending on app configuration):
- Google Play Services
- Firebase (Analytics, Crashlytics, Cloud Messaging, Auth)
